Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large wide #saucepan{} over high heat. Once hot,
add the @diced chicken thigh{260%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook,
stirring, until turning golden, ~{3-4%minutes}. Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Quarter
lengthways then thinly slice widthways. Add the @leek{1}(trimmed and sliced) and
the @mushrooms{150%g}(sliced) to the chicken with a knob of @?butter{knob}.
Cook, stirring, until starting to soften, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}) then add this to
the pan. Cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Pour the @boiling water{600%ml} into the pan. Stir in the @chicken stock powder{1}
and @penne pasta{200%g}, stir well. Bring to a simmer and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Cover with a #lid{} and cook, stirring every ~{2-3%minutes}, until the
penne is tender, ~{12%minutes}.

> Add a splash of water if it dries out.

While the pasta is cooking, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{½}(roughly chopped).

Once the pasta is cooked, add the @reduced fat creme fraiche{150%g} and
@?tarragon{} (add less if you don't like too much) to it and mix well. Taste and
add @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it. Divide between #bowls{} and
give a good grind of @black pepper{} as the garnish, enjoy!